# ChroPlexiGnosis Code Standards

## State Management
- Use `setState` for simple state management
- Avoid complex state management libraries initially
- Keep state as local as possible to where it's needed

## Data Models
- Create immutable data models with final fields when possible
- Use factory constructors for creating objects from JSON
- Implement `toString()` methods for easier debugging
- Do not use freezed package or part syntax

## File Organization
- Keep files focused on a single responsibility
- Limit file size to under 300 lines when possible
- Group related functionality in directories
- Use feature-first organization for screens and widgets

## Naming Conventions
- Use `camelCase` for variables and methods
- Use `PascalCase` for classes and enums
- Use `snake_case` for file names
- Prefix private members with underscore

## UI Development
- Extract reusable widgets to separate files
- Use constants for repeated values (dimensions, durations)
- Implement responsive layouts that work across device sizes
- Follow Material Design guidelines for spacing and sizing

## Performance
- Avoid expensive operations in build methods
- Use const constructors where appropriate
- Implement pagination or virtualization for large lists
- Minimize rebuilds by using efficient state management